    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix configuration mismatch handling for extended DCI PDU types in MAC scheduler\n\n### Summary\nThe MAC scheduler contained a configuration mismatch between protocol layers that caused inconsistent behavior when processing extended DCI PDU types (EPDCCH, MPDCCH, NPDCCH). The debug function `HI_DCI0_PDU_TYPE` correctly identified all PDU types, but several processing functions only handled the basic `NFAPI_HI_DCI0_DCI_PDU_TYPE`, leading to dropped DCI allocations for UEs using advanced scheduling modes.\n\nThis issue was particularly evident when testing with CE UEs that require MPDCCH-based DCI formats. The symptom was that DCI0 allocations would be created for these UEs but then ignored during RNTI verification and DL assignment index updates, causing UL transmission failures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_dlsch.c`: Updated `update_ul_dci()` to properly handle all DCI PDU types when setting DL assignment index\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Updated `get_V_UL_DAI()` to process extended DCI types consistently  \n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_ulsch.c`: Rewrote RNTI verification logic in `schedule_ulsch_rnti()` to access correct RNTI field for each PDU type\n\n"
}